[Elephant endotheliotropic herpesvirus 1A is a member of the _Proboscivirus_ genus and is a major cause of fatal hemorrhagic disease in endangered juvenile Asian elephants worldwide.

This virus causes fatal hemorrhagic disease and is commonly identified in animals kept at zoos. The virus only causes benign external herpetic lesions in African elephants, but in Asian elephant's infection results in endothelial disease, which in many cases can be fatal.

